       #include <stdio.h>

       FILE *tmpfile (void);

       FILE *tmpfile64 (void);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       tmpfile creates a temporary file using a name generated by
       the routine and returns a corresponding FILE pointer.   If
       the  file  cannot  be  opened, a NULL pointer is returned.
       The file is automatically deleted when the  process  using
       it  terminates  or  when  the file is closed.  The file is
       opened for update (``w+'').

